In Horace's age, it is here asserted, that the Romans usually took no breakfast. Of such a point minuter ex- amination for different periods may well be excused. From the epigrams of Martial, however, while it appears, that for general use he recommends the caseus Vestinus, (x111. 31,) we also learn that boys rising at a very early hour had that allowance in a cake or biscuit made for the purpose.
